{"/service/ndnp/njr/batch_njr_basil_ver02/data/sn85035720/00279529947/1908050202/0270.xml":{"full_text":"BUILD MINIATURE\nDAMS TO GUIDE THEM\nWASHINGTON, D. 0., May 2:\nEngineers the Panama Canal have\noriginated a novel method of deter\nmining the necessary construction of\ntlic dams that are to impound and\nguide the water supply for the big\ntfitch.\ni This is by building dams in mlnla\nJt.r.rp. In a wooden tank, 80 feet\n(long, six feet wide and eight feet\nJiigh, a section of dam Is construct\ned oue-twentleth the actual size. In\nto the tank are pumped materials\nunder conditions similar to those\nthat will exist In the dam itself. The\njuiniature section will be subjected\nto water pressure. Records will be\nJtept of the water percolation\nthrough the layers of soil, the de\ngree of saturation and the erosion\nof the embankment. When these\nare completed the engineers will\nknow exactly what sort of material\nlis required, the quantity and the\n\u00efncthod of construction for the big\n\u00ablams.\n\u03b9 Real estate news on Saturday.\nTENNIS CABINET\nRESUMES ACTIVITY\nWASHINGTON, D. 0., May 2\u00ee\u2014\nWith the return of warm weather\nI the meetings of the Tennis Cabinet\nhave been resumed on the court in\nthe rear of the White House office\nbuilding, and one new member has\nbeen initiated.\nThe Tennis* Cabinet is that favored\ncoterie 6f office holders and diplo\nmats that the President invites to\ntest rficquets with him about thr\u00e7e\nafternoons a week and, although\nthere are no minutes kept of the\nproceedings, there are those who as\nsert that much of the real business\nof the government is shaped upon\nthe chalk drawn rectangle.\nMEXICAN RAILWAY MERGER.\nNew York, May 2:\u2014According t\u00b0\nlocal trust company officials, nearly\nall of the American stockholders Of\nthe Mexican Central Hallway Com\npany and Uu) National Railroad Com\npany of Mexico have assented to the\nplan of tho Mexican government to\nmerge the roads under the name of\nthe National Railways of Mexico.\nCOX TIRE CUSHION\nPATENT APPLIED FOR.\n\u039b CUSHION to be pieced between the inuer-tube and shoe of all kinds\nof Automobile Tires. Is made of felt and fabric. The Cox Tire\nCuthlon has stood tests over all kinds of roads, and will stand the\nhardest kind of wear. If you have to buy a new tube a half-inck smalltr\nsize can be used, which means a big saving In cost.\nIf Will Help To\nStop Puncture\u00b7,\nStop blow-out\u00b7.\nStop that leak In your pocket boek.\nPrevent Inner tube\u00b7 from chafing.\nKeep the tire cool In hot weather.\nMake tires last much longer.\nMake automoblllng a pleasure.\nAny novice can place tho cushion >hoe.\nIt will prevent Inner tubes from being pinched.\nPRICE PER SET OF FOUR\n28\" or 30\". 110 32\". ST1 34\" \u00bbr 38\". .$12\nWhen you order give size and make of tires.\nManufactured by DAVID H. COX, Rah way, N. J.\n\u03af J|^____ L__1_. .1\nBOELDERS' 1ND CONTRACTORS' DIRECTORY.\nJ. \u039a. JENSEN,\nARCHITECT,\nOffice Strieker Building.\n138 Smith St., Perth Amboy, N. J.\nEclwarcl Koyen Co.j\nBEST LEHIGH COAL\nfBand and Portland Cement., Cement\nBuilding Blocks in All Shapes,\nTiling.\nSayre Ave. Tel. 811-J,\nCARL O. CHRISTEN8EN,\nMason mid Contractor,\nALL KINDS OF CEMENT\nWORK A SPECIALTY.\nCor. State and Patersou St.\nTel. 44li, Perth Amboy, \u039d J.\nGRAHAM McKEON,\nGeneral Contractors\nEXCAVATING, GRADING, ETC.\n\u2022snd, Gravel, Broken Stone, Carting, &c.\n*44 Smith Ht. 2\u0390(\u0399 New llrunnwlck Ave.\nTelephone 215-L, 180-R and 4\u00ab-J.\nJens Soronsen\nCARPENTER AND BUILDER.\nResidence and Shop,\n312 Washington St.\nL. D. Telephone 878-L.\nCARL DRESSLER,\nCarpenter and Builder.\nlobbing Promptly Attended To.\nI Park Ave., near New llrumwlck Ave.\n\u0391. M. Smith H. C. Smith, Jr.\nSanitary Plumbing\u00b7, Gaa, Steam Fit\ntin^\u00b7 and Tinning\u00b7. Slate and Slag: Roof-|\ning. Residence and shop. 23 Hall Ave. f\nTel. Connection, 4 60-W.\nIRA R. GROUSE,\nCarpenter and Builder.\nTelephone