0d48. \u00ce09, 110, 111 and\n112, block 04 B, on Brighton ave\nnue.\nJacob Stone to Isaac Bird, 15 lots\non the westerly side of Elm street.\nErnest Hancock to Howard Cot\ntrell, lot 5, block 20, on Jefferson\nstreet.\nIda M. Van Pelt to Bertha M. Se\nguine, lot l&M, block 4, on Rector\nstreet.\nCharles W. Winberg to Gus. A.\nDanlelson, lot 2, block 38, on Fay\nette street.\nMary I. Riley to Mary C. Farring\nton, lots 18%, 19, 20, 16, 17. 18\nand 14, block 101, on Washington\nand North First streets,\nEstate of Chris Hanson to Annie\nGrieve, lots 1 and 2, block 41, on\nMarket street.\nThe First P. A. Hebrew Mutual\nSociety to the Congregation of Shaa\nrey Tflloh, lots 39 and 40, block 83,\non Madison avenue.\nJames T. Woglom to Martin Pe\nterson, lot 2, block 8, on Water\nstreet.\nSamuel Belikovo to Tube Dia\nmond, lots 6 and 7, block 33, on\nCommerce street.\nRaritan Realty Company to the\nPeter Breldt Brewing Company, lot\n21, block 89, on Fayette street and\nSTew Brunswick avenue.\nNO ADVERTISING\u2014and, a Uttl\u00b7\nlater, NO STORE.\nBe an advertiser\u2014lo a word.\nThe 1 j Store\nIf it Is Tans Yon\nWant\nWe have them, for big\npeople and little people.\nThey are just the thing in\nfootwear thie season.\nI\ni\nt\n\u03b9\nt\n\nI\n\nI\nI\n\u03b9\n1\ni\n1\nMen's shoes and\nOxfords\nIn tan, vici and Russia\ncalf, lace or blucher, all the\nfashionable shapes, shoes\nthat sell regularly at 2.50;\nhero today at\n1.95\nBoys' Tan Shoes\nOf fine quality tan vici,\nmade on good fitting lasts,\nsizes to 13\u00a3, regular 1.25\nsellers, today at\n98c\nWoni's Tan Oxtords\nLight and dark shades,\nthe best values in town at\nJL.50 and 1.98\nInfant's Tan 8 hoes\nIn lace or button, very\ngood quality, velue 76c,spe\ncial today at\n60c\nTan Skoes and\nOxfords\nFor boys and girls, spe\ncially priced today.\n||yman^|fed88n\n226-7 SMITH ST.\nBOOSTERS IN\nORGANIZATION\nForm a National Prosperity As\nsociation in St. Louis-Faith\nin the Future Their Cry.\nTO KEEP DINNER PAIL FULL\nSt. Louis, May 2.\u2014A business organ\nization to be known ns the National\nProsperity Association of St. Louis lias\nbeen formed as the result of a confer\nence held by business men during the\nlast three days, and a formal address\nwas issued to the business Interests of\nthe country. It Is proposed to extend\nthe ramifications of the association\nthroughout the country for the better\nment of all classes of business. It Is\nstated that the association has for Its\nobject the encouragement of the return\nof prosperity and uplifting of business\nInterests generally.\nThe officers of the association com\nprising the executive committee are:\nChairman, E, C. Simmons, formerly\npresident of th\u00e7 Simmons Hardware\ncompany; vice chairman, AV. \u039a. Blxby,\nformerly president of tb\u00f4 American\nCar and Foundry company.\nPurpo\u00b7\u00b7 of the Association.\nIn the formal address it is set forth\nthat the purpose of the National Pros\nperity Association of St. Louis lei\nTo keep the dinner pall full, to keep\nthe pay car going, to keep the factory\nbusy, to keep workmen employed and\nmaintain present wages. The address\ncontinues\n\"The National Prosperity Association\nof St. Louis has nothing to do with the\npast. If looks forward. Jt Is not politi\ncal. It has a platform. The two planks\nare a square deal and a square meal\nfor every man. There Is nothing fun\ndamentally wrong with the business\nsituation. The financial clouds have\nrolled by, The cr\u00e7p prospects, that ba\nsis of all things for us, are exception\nally good. We believe that we can get\nba\u00e8k to normal conditions quickly if\nwe will. We do not see why we should\nwatt for the closing months of 1908 or\ntoi the spring of 1900.\n\"Commercial 8un la Shining.\"\n\"We have passed the low level. The\ncommercial sun Is shining. This Is the\nbusiness May day. The time for this\nmovement Is ripe right now. It was\nnot ripe before.\n\"The St. Louis movement may spread\nto other communities. We hope It will.\nThe prosperity we promote Is national.\nThe plane and methods of the National\nProsperity Assooiatlon of St. Louis nre\navailable to any business organization\nor any Individual anywhere. Our as\nsociation will welcome any helpful\nsuggestion to Increase its efficiency.\nWe are confident that Jf the business\nmen of the United States join In the\nSt. Coule movement prosperity will be\nat full tide before the end of the yeai\nand that 1009 will be the best business\nyear our country has known.\"\nChairman Simmons said:\n\"We have formed a business organi\nsation having for its object the encour\nagement of a return of prosperity\nlopner than might otherwise occui\nwithout help. We belleye that present\n:ondltlons are exceedingly favorable to\nthis.\"\nMOVING A TOWN IN THE\nPANAMA OANALZONE\nWASHINGTON, D. 0., May 2t\u2014\nneidentftl to the work ot digging\nhe Panama Canal, the engineers\nire preparing to pick up A village\nhat was so unfortunate as to es\nabllsh Itself in the path o\u00c7 progress.\nThis is the old town of Gatun,\nvhich has 110 buildings and a popu\natlon of 600, It is on the site of\nhe Qatun dam and will be can-led\niff two miles and set down along\nhe Panama railroad. In the oora\nuisslon's way of doing things, the\naovlng of a village is about as lm\niortant as amputating a wart.\nThe church and parsonage have\nlready been shipped to their new\ntome. The native school Is about to\nie moved and the natives are taking\nlown their houses and putting them\nin freight cars on whloh they will be\niauled to the new site at the ex\niense of the commission.\nThe only difficulty is that the na\n\u00efves who had lived in the present\nocatlon long before it became the\n}atun dam site, don't relish carry\nng oft their homes to tlie new piae*.\nf they don't, the commission will\nlo It for them. The new site Is the\n>nly one where the sewer and water\nforks have been installed before\nhe town. Everything Is now ready.\nTo hold an auction sale without\nidvertlslng it in this newspaper is\ntot to hold much of an auction sale\nTalk of The Hour\nOar excellent assortment of\nLawn Mowers.\nGarden Tools.\nLawn and Oarden\nSeed.\nOarden Hose.\nOil and One Stoves.\nKollytMeAlindoo\n74 Smith et.\nIf $16 is Your\nPrit\u00bb For \u03b2 Suif\nSee our suits before you let go\nof your money. We'll vouch for\nthe goodness we know Is in our\nclothes, and you can find just\nthe color and style you want,\nand in your size without having\nto wait for it.\nYour tailor will find it difficult\nto give you half as much modern\nstyle as you'll find in these gar\nments and besides he'll want a\nlot of time to make the suit.\nNo waiting here, your suit is\nready for you now.\nfltw lutA\u00f4 un\nDOG THEORIES\nWASHINGTON, D. C\u201e May 2:\nA report just issued by the Bureau\nof Animal Industry of the Depart\nment of Agriculture smashes a num\nber of long-cherished delusions en\ntertained by the great American pub\nlics. The document, written In \u03b5\npopular Vein, Is devoted to rabies\nana Its Increasing prevalence.\nIn the first place, It Is stated thai\nthe fixed (dea that a dog Buffering\nwith rabies avoids water as 11\nwould the devil, Is a big mistake and\nthat, as a matter of fact, diseased\nanimals crave water. The scientists\npooh-pooh the Idea that there ever\nwas any efficacy in the application of\n\"madstones\" to bites by dogs infect\ned with rabies. Also, it Is emphati\ncally declared that the so-called\n\"dog days\" of summer haven't a\nthing to do with the disease and that\nanimals are as likely to become in\nfected In December or any other\nmonth.\nThe report reiterates that there is\nonly one way in which to head off\nrabies in human beings once infec\ntion is known to have occurred, and\nthat Is either by the Pasteur or\nHogyes treatments.\nThere Is no possible way to be\ncome infected by the rabies, the re\nport says, except through being bit\nten by an animal suffering with the\nhorrible diseas\u00e8. And it is often\ndifficult to determine whether the\nbiter is really suffering with rabies,\nor whether the bitten will devaloi\nthe ghastly symptoms or ngt, It ii\nstated that the only w\u00e2y to eradi\ncate the plague of rabies la bjf s\nuniform muzzling of dogs.\nManZan Pile Remedy, price 50c, |l\nguaranteed. Put up ready to u\u00bbe.\nOne application prompt relief tp any\nform of piles. Sooth\u00e8e and heals.\nBold by Sexton, druggist.\nMen's\nTrousers\nGray or brown worsteds,\nin stripes or checks, well\nmade.\n$2.40\nValue $3.50\nP. Joselsoo Sod,\n338 State Street\nIt is Time to I\nChange Your\nUnderwear and\n\u03a4 opshirts\nThe best Negligee Shirt, dark;\nor light colors, from.. 49c up\nMen's Sox from 10c up\nMen's Undershirts and\nDrawers from 25c up\nMen's Suspenders and Belts \u03b9\nfrom 2 5c up\nKXxxxxooeeceoQcocQCXx:\nNathan\nJacobson\n318 State Street.\nBAILEY HUH I\nON IN TEXAS\nHouston, Tex., May 2:\u2014Whether\nUnited States Senator J. W. Bailey\nshall be sent to Denver as one of the\ndelegates-at-large from Texas la the\nQuestion to be determined at prim\naries to ba held throughout the state\ntoday. The fight between the Bailey\u00b7\u00b7\nltes and the anti-Batleyltes has been\nthe most momentous political strug\ngle since the republic of Texas enter.\ned the Union, and has been contested\nwith unprecedented bitterness by\nboth sides. Senator Bailey has beei;\nspeaking almost constantly for weeka\n;ind has made an almost superhumai\\\neffort to maintain his threatened\npolitical supremacy in Texas.\nPeril* In River Ice.\nAlbany, \u039d. Y., May 2.\u2014Zones of dan>\ng\u00e9rons pollution In the waters of the\nHudson and Mohawk rivers from\nwhich ice is harvested are reported to\nexist in (he vicinity of Albany, Troy,\nSchenectady aud other places alone\nthe upper Hudson and lower Mohawk\nvalleys lu a statement made public by\nthe state health department. \"The\ncutting of ice from these fields should\nbe prohibited,\" says the report.\nWast End Pharm